  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What percentage of commission do sellers need to pay e-commerce websites like Flipkart, eBay, Amazon, Shopclues, Shimply, Myntra etc., when selling clothing such as t-shirts?",
  "response": "The commission percentage that sellers need to pay on e-commerce platforms like Flipkart, eBay, Amazon, ShopClues, Shimply, Myntra, etc., varies depending on the platform, the category of the product, the seller's plan, and other factors. For clothing items like t-shirts, the commission typically ranges **between 10% to 25%**. Here's a general breakdown:\n\n1. **Amazon**:  \n   - Clothing categories typically incur a commission of **15%** of the total sale price (including shipping charges).  \n   - For certain subcategories, the commission may vary slightly.\n\n2. **Flipkart**:  \n   - Sellers in the fashion category (including t-shirts) pay a commission of **15% to 20%**, depending on the product type and seller plan.  \n   - Flipkart may also charge additional fees like shipping fees and fixed closing fees.\n\n3. **eBay**:  \n   - eBay charges a **final value fee** (commission) of **12.35%** for clothing categories.  \n   - Additional fees like insertion fees or payment processing fees may apply.\n\n4. **Myntra**:  \n   - Myntra charges a commission of **20% to 25%** for fashion items, including t-shirts.  \n   - This can vary based on brand agreements or seller plans.\n\n5. **ShopClues**:  \n   - ShopClues charges a commission of **10% to 15%** for clothing items.  \n   - Additional fees like shipping charges may apply.\n\n6. **Shimply**:  \n   - Shimply charges a commission of **20% to 25%** for lifestyle and fashion products, including t-shirts.  \n   - This may vary based on the seller's agreement.\n\n### Additional Fees to Consider:\n- **Shipping Fees**: Most platforms charge shipping fees or require sellers to offer free shipping.  \n- **Payment Gateway Fees**: Some platforms deduct payment processing fees (e.g., **2% to 4%**).  \n- **Fixed Closing Fees**: Platforms like Flipkart may charge a fixed closing fee per order.  \n- **Subscription Fees**: Platforms like Amazon or Flipkart may require sellers to subscribe to a plan (e.g., Amazon's Professional Selling Plan).\n\n### Tips for Sellers:\n- Check the platform's seller fee structure and policies before listing products.  \n- Consider the total cost (commission + fees) when pricing your products.  \n- Negotiate commissions if you\u2019re a bulk seller or a brand owner.\n\nFor the most accurate and updated information, it\u2019s best to refer to the specific platform\u2019s seller guidelines or contact their seller support team.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
